[
    {
        "content": "<p>Trying to port some older code to recent <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/commits/rust-dev\">rust-dev</a> (Linux 6.9-rc1 &amp; Rust 1.77.1) for the  <a href=\"https://github.com/Fabo/linux/commit/54a3c8ec56a4bb53d461e65b9866314a93f5be60#diff-912419f3b08a38cb2eed56dd0f06615b19f0f91d25c014a0aedf6d9be4da3d04R38\">code</a></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span>::<span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">try_resize</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I get</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0599</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"nc\">no</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">named</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">try_resize</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">current</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">scope</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">-</span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">io_buffer</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>:<span class=\"mi\">38</span>:<span class=\"mi\">14</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">38</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">try_resize</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">              </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">help</span>: <span class=\"nc\">there</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">similar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">name</span>: <span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">try_reserve</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>How does this <code>data.try_resize</code> can be \"translated\" to the recent kernel?</p>",
        "id": 433226922,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1713168407
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's called <code>resize</code> now.</p>",
        "id": 433227466,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1713168584
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/How.20to.20port.20Vec.20try_resize.28.29.20to.20recent.20kernel.3F/near/433227466\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It's called <code>resize</code> now.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Hmm?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0599</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"nc\">no</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">named</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">resize</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">current</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">scope</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">-</span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">io_buffer</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>:<span class=\"mi\">38</span>:<span class=\"mi\">14</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">38</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">resize</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">              </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 433228718,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1713168978
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You may need to import VecExt</p>",
        "id": 433229650,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1713169303
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/commit/68ef103b6b08bfad3f6b33d0888d84434482b5aa\">https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/commit/68ef103b6b08bfad3f6b33d0888d84434482b5aa</a></p>",
        "id": 433229829,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1713169354
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/How.20to.20port.20Vec.20try_resize.28.29.20to.20recent.20kernel.3F/near/433229829\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/commit/68ef103b6b08bfad3f6b33d0888d84434482b5aa\">https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/commit/68ef103b6b08bfad3f6b33d0888d84434482b5aa</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Sorry if I missed something. But that deals with with_capacity(), push(), extend_from_slice() and reserve(). And the removal of try_ for these. But nothing about <code>resize</code> (?)</p>",
        "id": 433265612,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1713180805
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, it's possible that we no longer have a <code>resize</code> function.</p>",
        "id": 433266038,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1713180909
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the code looks to me as if it could just be a single call to <code>with_capacity</code></p>",
        "id": 433266692,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1713181083
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, this code is what I'm trying to upstream in <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/all/20240415-alice-mm-v5-0-6f55e4d8ef51@google.com/\">this patchset</a></p>",
        "id": 433267175,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1713181217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So you should probably just use my patch. We may not have a <code>resize</code>, but we do have a <code>reserve</code>.</p>",
        "id": 433267445,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1713181305
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/How.20to.20port.20Vec.20try_resize.28.29.20to.20recent.20kernel.3F/near/433266692\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the code looks to me as if it could just be a single call to <code>with_capacity</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thanks! Just for the logs:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">diff</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">io_buffer</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">io_buffer</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"n\">index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">17</span><span class=\"n\">ebd6d24805</span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"n\">d8739def4fd0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">100644</span>\n<span class=\"o\">---</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">io_buffer</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">io_buffer</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">6</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">@@</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sd\">//! Buffers used in IO.</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span>::<span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span>::<span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">vec_ext</span>::<span class=\"n\">VecExt</span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span>::<span class=\"n\">error</span>::<span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">vec</span>::<span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">mem</span>::<span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">size_of</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">34</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">35</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">@@</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">is_empty</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kt\">bool</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Returns `EFAULT` if the address does not currently point to mapped, readable memory.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">read_all</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span>::<span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">try_resize</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span>::<span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u8</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>::<span class=\"n\">with_capacity</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GFP_KERNEL</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: The output buffer is valid as we just allocated it.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read_raw</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">data</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">len</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 433444775,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirk Behme",
        "timestamp": 1713245564
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that looks good if you just want to try things. Alice's version will soon land and then you can just use that.</p>",
